Filter.
    - used to format the data before "appending the View" based on application requirement.
    - In general we will apply the filters by using " | ".
    - we can apply more than one filter at a time to the view.
    - we have two types og filters.

        1.Custom Filters.

        2.Predefined Filters.


Custom Filters.
    - Creating our own filter based on application requirement called as Custom Filter.

Syntax.

       app.filter("name of filter" , "function to implement filter");

            //Implementation


       Ex.

            app.filter("reverse" , reverse);
            function reverse(){
                return function(arg1,arg2,arg3,......argn){
                        //Logic
                }
            }

Predefined Filters.

       - The Filters Given by the framework called as Predefined Filters.

1. orderBy.
    used to arrange the data either assending / decending order.


2.limitTo.


    Syntax.

        limitTo : 5

       Ex.
        <tr ng-repeat="x in data | orderBy:'id' | limitTo:3">
                    <td>{{x.id}}</td>
                    <td>{{x.name}}</td>
        </tr>


3.filter
    - used to filter the data based on the user input.

Ex.
<tr ng-repeat = "x in data | filter:'AngularJS'">

    //Logic Goes Here

</tr>

[ Note. it will search the whole table with the given input ]


4.uppercase.

    - it is used to convert the "lowercase characters" to "uppercase characters"

Ex.
 app.controller("ctrl" , ctrl);
 ctrl.$inject=["$scope"];
 function ctrl($scope){
    $scope.var_one = "i am from uppercase filter";
 }

 {{var_one}} //i am from uppercase filter
 {{var_one | uppercase }} //I AM FROM UPPERCASE FILTER


  5.lowercase.
     - it is used to convert the "uppercase characters" to "lowercase characters".


    $scope.var_two = "HELLO";
    {{var_two | lowercase}} //hello


 6.currency
     - used to append the "$" symbol to the numerical values.

     Ex.

        $scope.var_three = 100;


        {{var_three}} //100
        {{var_three | currency}} // $100.00
        {{var_three | currency : "$" : 4}} //$100.0000
        {{var_three | currency : "₹" : 2}} //₹100.00


 7. date.
         - used to format the date accroding to application requirement.

         $scope.var_four = new Date();
         {{var_four}}                           //"2017-05-22T02:46:14.658Z"
         {{var_four | date:'medium' }}          // May 22, 2017 8:17:10 AM
         {{var_four | date:'fullDate'}}         // Monday, May 22, 2017
         {{var_four | date:'short'}}            // 5/22/17 8:19 AM
         {{var_four | date:'dd-MM-yy'}}         // 22-05-17
         {{var_four | date:'dd-MM-yyyy'}}       // 22-05-2017
         {{var_four | date: 'MM-dd-yyyy'}}      // 05-22-2017











































